Package projects.pqueue.lists

Interface List<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of object that the List will hold.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DoublyLinkedList, LinkedList, StaticArrayList
    public interface List<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>

    List is a linear ADT which offers insertion, search and deletion in at most linear time. Elements can only be added to the front or the back, never in between.

    The interface is Iterable, which means that we can use for-each loops to easily access its elements. You would benefit from studying how iterator() is implemented.

    You should not edit this class! It is given to you as a resource for your project.

    Author:
    Jason Filippou
    See Also:
    LinkedList, DoublyLinkedList, iterator()
